                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/1440: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-12T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 12, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 12—3:08
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>330. Legation’s March 1, noon.<note n="94" xml:id="d616fn94">Not printed.</note>
                    General <persName corresp="#p_SC1">Shang Chen</persName> who has just arrived
                    here from Loyang stated that the Central Executive Committee after considerable
                    discussion decided to avoid Soviet alliance and to take measures to guard
                    against communist activities. Chinese fear eventually getting the worst of such
                    a bargain. The General confirms decision to continue resistance to Japan.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
